  "texts": [
    "The key findings of the reviews were classified into the four main thematic AI application areas (see Fig. 1).",
    "More than half of the reviews (54.5%, n = 36) discussed applications related to adaptive systems and personalisation, closely followed by profiling and prediction (48.5%, n = 32), 39.4% (n = 26) discussed findings related to assessment and evaluation, and only 21.2% (n = 14) looked into intelligent tutoring systems.",
    "The key findings will now be synthesised below.",
    "All of the reviews on adaptive systems (n = 36) are situated at the teaching and learning level, with only 12 reviews (33.3%) reporting findings for the administrative and institutional level.",
    "Five subcategories were found: chatbots/virtual assistants (n = 20), providing personalised content (n = 14), facial recognition/mood detection (n = 9), recommender systems/course scheduling (n = 5), and robots (n = 3)."
  ],
